article.headline: Delaware St. 75, Hampton 64
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Jahsha Bluntt scored 24 points to lead Delaware State to a 75-64 win against Hampton on Saturday for the Hornets' sixth straight win. Troy Roundtree and Roy Bright had 14 points for the Hornets (9-9, 6-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). The Hornets lead the MEAC. Michael Freeman led the Pirates (6-11, 3-4 MEAC) with 15 points. Rashad West added 13 points, and Vincent Simpson had 11 points. The Pirates took an early lead in the opening minutes, but the Hornets took control with a 10-4 run and never gave up the lead. Before halftime, the Pirates pulled within three 24-21 after an 11-4 run, but Delaware State came back with their own 10-0 run. At halftime, Delaware State led 43-30. The Hornets built a 20-point lead in the second half.
